{"id": "t_d9050e8c-a9b9-4be5-a2b8-1dd6eddac1e8", "edus": [{"text": "Hello there, do you listen to the radio much?", "speaker": "agent_1"}, {"text": "Sometimes, I would say Im more into podcasts, but I hear that Jupiter has some strong radio storms that can be picked up on AM radio", "speaker": "agent_2"}, {"text": "Yeah isn't that awesome, those must be some crazy storms!", "speaker": "agent_1"}, {"text": "How about you, what do you like to listen to on the radio", "speaker": "agent_2"}, {"text": "I do, I recently found a good local station that I really like, lots of oldies. ", "speaker": "agent_1"}, {"text": "Im not a fan of some of today' music, so I would agree with you there..  There is a website where you can listen to radio dramas for free, if you enjoy that sort of thing.", "speaker": "agent_2"}, {"text": "Yeah I would totally agree there.  And that is so cool, I bet there are so many hidden gems you could enjoy.", "speaker": "agent_1"}, {"text": "There probably are, some like the Finnish station that has an entire broadcast in classical Latin, might be a bit hard to understand for most people.  lol", "speaker": "agent_2"}, {"text": "I agree, I don't think too many people understand Latin these days, I know I wouldn't have any clue. ", "speaker": "agent_1"}, {"text": "Same here.  Do you know how soldiers made foxhole radios during WW2", "speaker": "agent_2"}, {"text": "No I don't, but it sounds very interesting.  How did they do it?", "speaker": "agent_1"}, {"text": "They used a razorblade and a pencil as the diode.  Pretty inventive.", "speaker": "agent_2"}, {"text": "That is very inventive and rather genius actually.  I guess any kind of entertainment was cherished. ", "speaker": "agent_1"}, {"text": "It was probably also a good way for them to get their news.", "speaker": "agent_2"}, {"text": "That too for sure, on a different subject, do you watch fox news at all?", "speaker": "agent_1"}, {"text": "I do not.  I tend to find them a bit slanted in their views.", "speaker": "agent_2"}, {"text": "I couldn't agree more, I didn't know how much more popular than the other networks they were though. ", "speaker": "agent_1"}, {"text": "It is kind of shocking.  I think it is funny they threatened to sue the simpsons for how the parody them", "speaker": "agent_2"}, {"text": "That is too funny, and the fact that at one point they were considering starting an all simpsons channel!", "speaker": "agent_1"}, {"text": "I could get behind that, but likely only for a few days.", "speaker": "agent_2"}, {"text": "I could, but only if they promised to only air the first 12 seasons or so, after that, no thank you. ", "speaker": "agent_1"}, {"text": "I havent watched much of the recent stuff as I cut my cable almost 3 years ago.", "speaker": "agent_2"}, {"text": "I think you are like a lot of other people out there.  Well it was nice talking, I hope you have a good day. ", "speaker": "agent_1"}], "discourse_structure": ["", "QA_PAIR(1, 2)", "COMMENT(2, 3)", "ALTERNATION(3, 4)", "QA_PAIR(4, 5)", "COMMENT(5, 6) ELABORATION(5, 6)", "COMMENT(6, 7) ELABORATION(6, 7)", "COMMENT(7, 8) ELABORATION(7, 8)", "COMMENT(8, 9) ELABORATION(8, 9)", "COMMENT(9, 10) QA_PAIR(10, 10)", "COMMENT(9, 11) QA_PAIR(10, 11)", "EXPLANATION(10, 12) NARRATION(10, 12)", "COMMENT(12, 13) ELABORATION(12, 13)", "COMMENT(13, 14) ELABORATION(13, 14)", "COMMENT(13, 15) ALTERNATION(13, 15) QA_PAIR(13, 15)", "QA_PAIR(15, 16) COMMENT(15, 16) ELABORATION(15, 16)", "COMMENT(16, 17) ELABORATION(16, 17)", "COMMENT(17, 18) ELABORATION(17, 18)", "COMMENT(18, 19) ELABORATION(18, 19)", "COMMENT(19, 20) ELABORATION(19, 20)", "COMMENT(20, 21) ELABORATION(20, 21)", "COMMENT(20, 22) ELABORATION(20, 22)", "COMMENT(20, 23) ELABORATION(20, 23)"]}
